Interpretation:
  full_m1_enclosure_ok means the access point has enough A2 M1 metal for default VIA1 M1 enclosure.
  inside_m1_but_enclosure_tight means the access point is on the pin but too close to an M1 pin edge.
  If most points are full_m1_enclosure_ok, the remaining off-grid is less likely pure LEF pin-metal width.
  Then focus should move to generated via/access snapping or route/check grid policy.
